Seeing the Big Picture;Changing and Improving;Making Effective Decisions;Leading and Communicating;Collaborating and Partnering;Building Capability for All;Achieving Commercial Outcomes;Delivering Value for Money;Managing a Quality Service;Delivering at Pace

Seeing the big picture is about having an in-depth understanding and knowledge of how your role fits with and supports organisational objectives and the wider public needs. For all staff, it is about focusing your contribution on the activities which will meet Civil Service goals and deliver the greatest value. At senior levels, it is about scanning the political context and taking account of wider impacts to develop long term implementation strategies that maximise opportunities to add value to the citizen and support economic, sustainable growth. ;People who are effective in this area are responsive, innovative and seek out opportunities to create effective change. For all staff, it‟s about being open to change, suggesting ideas for improvements to the way things are done, and working in „smarter‟, more focused ways. At senior levels, this is about creating and contributing to a culture of innovation and allowing people to consider and take managed risks. Doing this well means continuously seeking out ways to improve policy implementation and build a leaner, more flexible and responsive Civil Service. It also means making use of alternative delivery models including digital and shared service approaches wherever possible. ;Effectiveness in this area is about being objective, using sound judgement, evidence and knowledge to provide accurate, expert and professional advice. For all staff, it means showing clarity of thought, setting priorities, analysing and using evidence to evaluate options before arriving at well reasoned justifiable decisions. At senior levels, leaders will be creating evidence based strategies, evaluating options, impacts, risks and solutions. They will aim to maximise return while minimising risk and balancing social, political, financial, economic and environmental considerations to provide sustainable outcomes. ;At all levels, effectiveness in this area is about leading from the front and communicating with clarity, conviction and enthusiasm. It‟s about supporting principles of fairness of opportunity for all and a dedication to a diverse range of citizens. At senior levels, it is about establishing a strong direction and a persuasive future vision, managing and engaging with people with honesty and integrity, and upholding the reputation of the Department and the Civil Service. ;People skilled in this area create and maintain positive, professional and trusting working relationships with a wide range of people within and outside the Civil Service to help get business done. At all levels, it requires working collaboratively, sharing information and building supportive, responsive relationships with colleagues and stakeholders, whilst having the confidence to challenge assumptions. At senior levels, it‟s about delivering business objectives through creating an inclusive environment, encouraging collaboration and building effective partnerships including relationships with Ministers. ;Effectiveness in this area is having a strong focus on continuous learning for oneself, others and the organisation. For all staff, it‟s being open to learning, about keeping one‟s own knowledge and skill set current and evolving. At senior levels, it‟s about talent management and ensuring a diverse blend of capability and skills is identified and developed to meet current and future business needs. It‟s also about creating a learning and knowledge culture across the organisation to inform future plans and transformational change. ;Being effective in this area is about maintaining an economic, long-term focus in all activities. For all, it‟s about having a commercial, financial and sustainable mindset to ensure all activities and services are delivering added value and working to stimulate economic growth. At senior levels, it‟s about identifying economic, market and customer issues and using these to promote innovative business models, commercial partnerships and agreements to deliver greatest value, and ensuring tight commercial controls of finances, resources and contracts to meet strategic priorities. ;Delivering value for money involves the efficient, effective and economic use of taxpayers‟ money in the delivery of public services. For all staff, it means seeking out and implementing solutions which achieve the best mix of quality and effectiveness for the least outlay. People who do this well base their decisions on evidenced information and follow agreed processes and policies, challenging these appropriately where they appear to prevent good value for money. At senior levels, effective people embed a culture of value for money within their area/function. They work collaboratively across boundaries to ensure that the Civil Service maximises its strategic outcomes within the resources available. ;Effectiveness in this area is about being organised to deliver service objectives and striving to improve the quality of service, taking account of diverse customer needs and requirements. People who are effective plan, organise and manage their time and activities to deliver a high quality and efficient service, applying programme and project management approaches to support service delivery. At senior levels, it is about creating an environment to deliver operational excellence and creating the most appropriate and cost effective delivery models for public services. ;Effectiveness in this area means focusing on delivering timely performance with energy and taking responsibility and accountability for quality outcomes. For all staff, it‟s about working to agreed goals and activities and dealing with challenges in a responsive and constructive way. At senior levels, it is about building a performance culture to deliver outcomes with a firm focus on prioritisation and addressing performance issues resolutely, fairly and promptly. It is also about leaders providing the focus and energy to drive activities forward through others and encourage staff to perform effectively during challenging and changing times.

The Ethnographic Atlas (EA) describes cultural practices for 1291 societies, ranging from societies with complex agricultural economies and political systems to small hunter-gatherer groups. The societies are globally distributed with especially good coverage of Africa and western North America.
;Binford Hunter-Gatherer dataset describes cultural practices for 339 hunter-gatherer groups. Approximately two-thirds of the societies described by Binford are also described in the EA. However, the Binford database includes a number of societies not in the EA, including many in Australia and northern North America.
;The Standard Cross-Cultural Sample (SCCS) describes a subset of 186 societies that also appear in the EA. These 186 societies were chosen by George P. Murdock, the creator of the dataset, with the goal of maximizing independence among societies. The societies are globally distributed. Since the first installment of the SCCS was published by Murdock and Morrow in 1970, many others have followed, each typically focused on a particular theme (e.g., childhood, kinship systems). Over 2000 cultural variables have now been coded for the 186 societies in the SCCS.
;The Western North American Indians (WNAI) dataset describes cultural practices for 172 societies in Western North America. There is significant overlap between the societies described in the WNAI and those in the other three datasets, however the WNAI includes approximately 20 societies not described in the other datasets.

Forte no ano passado, o elenco do Palmeiras foi ainda mais reforçado em 2018. Ganhou boas opções nas laterais, setor mais deficiente até a última temporada, e passou a ter nada menos do que Lucas Lima como seu armador. Uma potência nas mãos do técnico Roger Machado.;Campeão da Libertadores e da Recopa, o elenco do Grêmio chega turbinado por quatro craques, além de outros que jogam muito. Ainda conta com um time bem orquestrado por Renato e que promete brigar por todos os títulos.;O Cruzeiro chega com um dos favoritos ao Brasileiro, principalmente pela força do seu grupo. Em todos os setores, o time tem jogadores de renome e com títulos importantes, tendo necessidades secundárias de reforços. Lesionado, o atacante Fred só volta no fim do ano e fica fora da avaliação.;Campeão estadual e nacional no ano passado, o Corinthians começou 2018 conquistando mais um título do Paulistão. Com um nível um pouco abaixo de 2017 pela perda de seu artilheiro Jô, o clube chega ao Brasileirão com um elenco forte, mas sem uma grande estrela.;O maior investimento foi Henrique Dourado. Por não ter se reforçado tanto, ao menos manteve a espinha dorsal do time. Outra aposta rubro-negra está no meia colombiano Marlos, que pouco jogou e ainda não se destacou. Guerrero, suspenso por doping, deve retornar após a Copa, já que o Fla manifestou interesse de estender o contrato.;No jovem e veloz time dos Meninos da Vila, craque incontestável mesmo é o goleiro (Vanderlei). Gabigol pode até carregar esse status fora de campo, mas tem deixado a desejar. E Bruno Henrique, que se recupera de lesão no olho direito, tenta retornar ao time já em maio.;Em um ano de reformulação, o Atlético-MG entra no Brasileiro correndo por fora. O goleiro Victor e o atacante Ricardo Oliveira são os pontos de segurança do time. A equipe conta ainda com outras peças experientes, mas a diretoria admite a necessidade de buscar reforços.;O São Paulo não vive mais aqueles tempos de elencos equilibrados e talentosos. O clube entra no Brasileirão alicerçado em veteranos que já viveram dias melhores – casos de Diego Souza e Nenê – e apostando em novidades como Liziero e Valdívia.;Em ano de reconstrução e de volta à Série A, o Inter mostra nova identidade sob comando de Odair Hellmann. Chega para o Brasileirão com desconfiança por conta da eliminação precoce no Gauchão. O maior objetivo é o de se manter.;O elenco vascaíno tem uma mescla de experiência e juventude, e terá novidades caseiras para o Brasileiro, como Breno, Kelvin e Ramon, que se recuperam de lesão, além do volante Bruno Silva, que não jogou o Carioca. Machucado, Paulinho é a grande perda para o início da competição.;O ponto forte do Botafogo é no gol. A ostentação debaixo das balizas, com Gatito e Jefferson, vai na contramão do elenco enxuto. O time não é dos mais badalados e deve ficar no meio da tabela, mas a união do grupo pode fazer o Alvinegro se superar e alçar voos maiores. Lesionado, João Paulo fica fora da avaliação.;Fluminense tem uma time jovem, com boas figuras neste começo de ano: Ibañez, Aytor Lucas e Pedro, artilheiro do Carioca, com sete gols. Jadson e Sornoza comandam o meio, e o banco de reservas é um problema, afinal, há poucas opções a Abel.;A Chape manteve boa parte do elenco que conquistou uma vaga na Libertadores em 2017. Além disso, fez contratações pontuais, como Márcio Araújo e Guilherme. A força do conjunto é a principal arma do clube, mas Canteros desponta na parte técnica.;O Bahia manteve peças de destaque da temporada passada e se reforçou para 2018. Contratado no início do ano, o lateral-direito Nino é uma das armas ofensivas da equipe comandada por Guto Ferreira. Vinícius vive grande fase. Ele e Gregore são os pilares do meio-campo tricolor.;Sem estrelas e poucas promessas, o Atlético-PR apresenta um elenco que não chama atenção na individualidade, mas também não possui muitos jogadores que podem dar aquele susto na torcida. A defesa tem os nomes com mais força, entre eles, o goleiro Santos e o zagueiro Thiago Heleno. O ataque é o lado mais frágil, sem nenhum nome que seja o diferencial.;O Ceará manteve a base do time que subiu à Série A. Em 2018, reforçou todos os setores. Para este Brasileirão, a única perda é Andrigo, negociado pelo Inter com o Sport. O elenco não briga nas cabeças, mas é constante e deve ficar pelo meio da tabela.;O América-MG tem o objetivo de não ser rebaixado. A defesa é o grande trunfo para isso. A segurança de João Ricardo e o entrosamento de Messias e Rafael Lima se destacam. O problema está no ataque, que ainda busca um jogador para render bem ao lado de Aylon. Rafael Moura apresentou crescimento na reta final do Mineiro.;O time passa por um processo de reformulação. Perdeu nomes como o volante Rithely, o meia Diego Souza e o atacante André. Com dificuldades financeiras, buscou no mercado nomes menos badalados e tem, neste ano, objetivos menos audaciosos para quem já sonhou com vaga na Libertadores.;A defesa é motivo de dor de cabeça para o Vitória. O sistema de marcação foi vazado na maioria dos jogos do primeiro semestre e levou a diretoria rubro-negra a buscar reforços para corrigir o problema. Em contrapartida, o ataque tem funcionado bem. Neilton é o destaque da equipe, com 13 gols marcados.;O Paraná apostou em contratações após o fracasso no Paranaense e trouxe jogadores que ainda são incógnitas, como Luan, que chegou dos Emirados Árabes e Caio Henrique, contratado do Atlético de Madrid, mas que apenas jogou a Série B do Espanhol.  〜歡迎大家等下光臨松菸護樹現場;另外，今早8：30，將於台北市政府大門口召開［為台北機廠世界級鐵道文化資產與老樹請命］記者會，請大家到場聲援（行動發起：搶救北廠聯盟、台灣護樹團體聯盟、松菸公園催生聯盟）;最新消息「市府路型變更公文：要移除樹不保留！」市府明天開的協調會〜根本是摸頭大會！市府決定的協調方案竟然是：光復南路的人行道-印度紫檀〜移除、分隔島的木棉樹〜移除;今天的專題報導，接著前幾天討論的糧食、能源、水，將談論到水資源的議題。
 
 現代由於工業、農業等各類用水都出現了大幅度的成長，我們現在正以極快的速度消耗地球上可用的水資源。聯合國估計，2030年，估計世界上將有47%的人口居住在用水高度緊張的地區。台灣雖然平均每年都有2000多毫米的降雨量，台灣仍然是世界排名第十八的缺水地區。;
我國設計的減碳四法包含「再生能源發展條例」、「能源管理法」、「能源稅條例（草案）」及「溫室氣體減量法（草案）」，而在民國九十八年六月已完成「再生能源發展條例」的立法， 「能源管理法」部分條文也已修正。
 
 有關各法詳細內容，請參閱行政院環保署的網站：http://estc10.estc.tw/ghgrule/KnowRule/rule-1.asp;昨天的圖像中，由左至右依序為：台灣碳標籤、環保標章、環保公園標誌與垃圾強制分類，各位金頭腦們答對了嗎= )
 
 其中，大眾比較陌生的是環保公園標誌，公園若有這個標誌，表示這個公園具有環境保護、環境教育或環保相關工作的研發等機能。
 
 另外，在行政院環保署的網頁中，還有其它相關的標章／標誌喔：http://www.epa.gov.tw/ch/artshow.aspx?busin=4097&art=2009122915063261&path=13599;

'];['Prefeito dá posse aos novos secretários.            
'];['Prefeitura terá expediente interno até quarta.            
'];['Prefeito cria Grupo de Trabalho para ações emergenciais.            
'];['Rossano e Karen tomam posse em São Gabriel e destacam meta de restaurar as finanças            
']

['O primeiro dia de 2017 marcou o início de uma nova gestão à frente do Poder Executivo Municipal e de novas legislaturas em todo o país. Em São Gabriel, o ato de posse foi realizado às 16 horas, na Câmara Municipal de Vereadores, com a posse dos novos parlamentares e também do prefeito municipal, Rossano Dotto Gonçalves, e sua vice, Karen Lannes. \xa0 \xa0',
,
, 'O ato de instalação da legislatura foi presidido pelo parlamentar mais idoso, vereador Evaristo de Oliveira Guedes (PPS), como determina a legislação. Os vereadores prestaram o juramento estabelecido pela Lei Orgânica e entregaram os diplomas expedidos pela Justiça Eleitoral e a declaração de bens. Em seguida, foi realizada a eleição da Mesa Diretora, que foi quem deu posse ao prefeito e à vice, mediante a leitura do Juramento estabelecido em lei.',
,
, 'Em seu pronunciamento, o prefeito empossado falou do seu compromisso com o reequilíbrio das contas públicas, com a já efetuada redução do número de secretarias, que será seguida por corte de cargos em comissão, economia de despesas e mudança do perfil da dívida, tendo como prioridade o diagnóstico da situação da prefeitura, nos primeiros dias. “Estamos muito cientes da responsabilidade que nos foi delegada, mas também confiantes, porque acreditamos que São Gabriel tem jeito”, assinalou. ',
,
];['A palavra de ordem é: comprometimento e respeito à coisa pública. Com este imperativo, o Prefeito Municipal de São Gabriel, Rossano Dotto Gonçalves, deu posse aos secretários municipais da Gestão 2017/2020 na manhã desta segunda-feira, 02 de Janeiro, no saguão do Palácio Plácido de Castro, um dia depois da posse constitucional realizada na Câmara de Vereadores. ',
,
, 'Na ocasião, juntamente com a vice-prefeita Karen Lannes, o prefeito municipal deu posse aos secretários Valdemir Jobim (Administração), Rafael Gonçalves (Gabinete), Artur Goularte (Fazenda), Clóbis Saccol (Jurídico), Ricardo Júnior (Planejamento), Ricardo Coirolo (Saúde), Sildo Cabreira (Educação), Marcos Vieira (Obras), Juliana Medeiros (Indústria e Comércio), Antônio Pedro “Pepeca” Bertazzo (Serviços Urbanos), Carlos Cléber Dias Leal (Agricultura) e Karen Lannes (Assistência Social). ',
,
, 'Alguns secretários tomaram posse também respondendo por outras pastas que serão extintas ou fundidas na futura reforma administrativa. É o caso de Rafael Gonçalves, do Gabinete, que acumula a pasta de Gestão e Relações Comunitárias, Juliana Medeiros, da Indústria e Comércio, que será fundida com a pasta do Turismo, e Carlos Cléber Leal,da Agricultura, que irá absorver a secretaria de Viação e Transportes. ',
,
, 'O Chefe de Gabinete, Rafael Gonçalves, falando em nome dos secretários empossados, destacou a importância da união e da lealdade ao projeto por parte de todos. “Como o prefeito Rossano costuma dizer, precisaremos de comprometimento. Não apenas entre nós, integrantes da gestão, mas especialmente comprometimento com o projeto escolhido pela vontade da população”, ressaltou.',
,
, 'O prefeito Rossano enfatizou que a nova equipe de trabalho irá levantar a situação de cada pasta da prefeitura em um amplo diagnóstico, e trabalhará para honrar a folha de pagamento do funcionalismo do mês de dezembro, que não foi paga na administração anterior. “Estamos cientes que vamos encontrar pela frente muita desestruturação, mas estamos motivados, temos uma equipe preparada e entusiasmada pra fazer valer o cumprimento dos nossos compromissos”, ressaltou.',
,
, 'Após a nomeação dos secretários, foi realizado um Culto Ecumênico, com bênção proferida pelo Bispo Jairo Minho, superintendente regional da Igreja do Evangelho Quadrangular, e o Pastor Claudiomiro Borges, da Igreja Evangélica Nova Aliança, juntamente com os pastores Leonardo Medina (Associação Missionária Luz das Nações), Rogério Ataíde (Igreja do Evangelho Quadrangular do Bairro Bom Fim) e Cláudio Moreira (Igreja do Evangelho Quadrangular em Vila Nova do Sul). ',
,
,
];['Com o propósito de averiguar todos os documentos, convênios e o estado das finanças públicas,\xa0 o Prefeito Rossano Gonçalves estabeleceu expediente interno para todos os setores administrativos das secretarias municipais,de segunda até quarta-feira, 04 de janeiro. A decisão foi oficializada através do Decreto Executivo 017/2017.',
,
, 'A decisão não afeta o atendimento do Serviço de Atendimento ao Contribuinte – SAC, no Centro Administrativo Eudóxia Garcia Chagas, nos fundos da prefeitura, que prossegue normalmente.',
,
, ' “Este período é necessário para que as secretarias façam um detalhado levantamento de toda a documentação, dos serviços e programas em andamento”, ressaltou o Chefe do Executivo.',
,
,
];['Além de traçar o diagnóstico do atual estado da máquina pública, tarefa em que estão envolvidas todas as secretarias, o novo Governo Municipal precisa também realizar ações urgentes para recuperação de vias urbanas, estradas, escolas e outros equipamentos públicos. Para isso, o Prefeito Municipal Rossano Gonçalves instituiu, no primeiro dia de trabalho na nova gestão, um Grupo de Trabalho que reúne secretarias estratégicas, para acompanhamento diário das ações emergenciais.',
,
, 'O Grupo de Trabalho para Ações Emergenciais reúne os secretários Marcos Vieira (Obras), Antônio Pedro “Pepeca” Bertazzo (Serviços Urbanos), Carlos Cléber Dias Leal (Transportes) e Artur Goularte (Fazenda). O grupo se reunirá diariamente com o Prefeito Municipal, para acompanhamento das ações, levantamento das necessidades e determinar os serviços e despesas necessários.',
,
, '“A comunidade aguarda resultados, e por isso, enquanto a gestão se organiza, é necessário fazer frente aos desafios mais urgentes, tarefa que vai caber mais diretamente a este grupo”, ressaltou.',
];['O primeiro dia de 2017 marcou o início de uma nova gestão à frente do Poder Executivo Municipal e de novas legislaturas em todo o país. Em São Gabriel, o ato de posse foi realizado às 16 horas, na Câmara Municipal de Vereadores, com a posse dos novos parlamentares e também do prefeito municipal, Rossano Dotto Gonçalves, e sua vice, Karen Lannes. \xa0 \xa0',
,

Os vereadores prestaram o juramento estabelecido pela Lei Orgânica e entregaram os diplomas expedidos pela Justiça Eleitoral e a declaração de bens. Em seguida, foi realizada a eleição da Mesa Diretora, que foi quem deu posse ao prefeito e à vice, mediante a leitura do Juramento estabelecido em lei.',
,
, 'Em seu pronunciamento, o prefeito empossado falou do seu compromisso com o reequilíbrio das contas públicas, com a já efetuada redução do número de secretarias, que será seguida por corte de cargos em comissão, economia de despesas e mudança do perfil da dívida, tendo como prioridade o diagnóstico da situação da prefeitura, nos primeiros dias. “Estamos muito cientes da responsabilidade que nos foi delegada, mas também confiantes, porque acreditamos que São Gabriel tem jeito”, assinalou. ',
,
, 'Redação: Pr. Cláudio Moreira (MTb/DRT-RS/010499)',

海色の輝石;ならず者から得た情報をもとに、姬塔たちは洞窟を訪れていた。宝石魔術を使う者の使命として宝石の闇取引など決して許さないと熱く語るレ・フィーエに、突如現れた魔物が襲いかかる。;ならず者達から事情を聞き出した一行は、
彼らが海色の輝石を見つけたという
洞窟を訪れていた。;許せませんわ……
伝説の宝石を手に入れて、
闇のルートで売りさばこうなんて！;闇商人達の取り締まりを
強化しないといけませんわね。
後で宝石境に手紙を出さないと……;ふぅん……
宝石境は宝石の闇取引の
取り締まりもやってるんだな。;ふん……当然ですわ。
宝石境に生きる者は、
輝石の輝きと共に生きる者ですもの。;宝石に護られ、宝石を護る。
それが宝石魔術を使う者の使命ですわ。;宝石は私達に力を与えてくれますの……
だからこそ、宝石には感謝をもって
接しなければなりませんのよ。;だというのに……
貴重な宝石で荒稼ぎしようなど、
まったくもって言語道断ですわ！;ま、まぁまぁ……
でも、これで私達も
伝説の宝石を見つけられそうですね！;ええ……先ほどの方々いわく、
この洞窟にあるのは、
間違いないらしいですけど……;グォォォォォッ！;そう簡単には、
お目にかからせて
くれないようですわね！;この程度の魔物、
私の華麗な宝石魔術で、
蹴散らして差し上げますわ！

海色的辉石;根据从暴徒们手中得来的消息、姬塔他们拜访了洞窟。作为宝石魔法使用者，绝不允许宝石的暗中交易，蕾·芬耶这么热切地说着，突然出现的魔物袭击了他们。;从暴徒中打探到消息的一行人、
来到了能找到海色的辉石的
洞窟。;无法原谅……
得到传说中的宝石、
通过黑色渠道卖出去什么的！;必须要强化暗商
的取缔工作啊。
之后一定要给宝石境寄信过去了……;唔……
宝石境也在做着取缔の
宝石的暗中交易之事啊。;哼……这可是当然。
在宝石境生活的人、
都是和辉石的光辉共存之人。;被宝石守护着、与此同时守护着宝石。
这就是宝石魔法使用者的使命。;宝石赋予我们力量……
正因如此、一定要对宝石满怀
感激之情。;尽管这样……
用贵重的宝石来赚钱什么的、
真是岂有此理！;是、是呢……
但是、这样来看
我们应该也能找到传说中的宝石呢！;嗯……就像之前的各位说的那样、
应该在这个洞窟里没错了……;吼哦哦哦哦哦！;好像是不会让我这么简单就见到呢！;这种程度的魔物、
就让我用华丽的宝石魔法来轻松打倒吧！;scene_chr067_q2_s10

My hope lay in Jack's promise that he would keep a bright light burning in the upper story to guide me on my course. On a clear night this light was visible from the village, but somehow or other I failed to take into account the state of the weather. The air was full of eddying flakes, which would render the headlight of a locomotive invisible a hundred yards distant. Strange that this important fact never occurred to me until I was fully a fourth of a mile from the village. Then, after looking in vain for the beacon light, the danger of my situation struck me, and I halted.
"I am certain to go wrong," I said to myself.
"It is out of my power to follow a direct course without something to serve as a compass. The "nipperkins" were a pair of handled cups which the children supposed to be silver, and which they always used at table.

It was strictly a family gathering, yet the room was quite full. Mr. Dinsmore was there with his wife, his daughter Elsie and her children, Edward and Zoe, Elsie Leland with her husband and babe, Violet Raymond with her husband's two little girls, Lulu and Grace, and lastly Rosie and Walter.
Everybody had a kindly greeting for the captain, and Violet's bright face grew still brighter as she made room for him on the sofa by her side.
"We were beginning to wonder what was keeping you," she said.
"Yes, I'm afraid I am rather behind time," he returned. "I hope you have not delayed your tea for me, Mrs. Dinsmore."
"No, it is but just ready," she said. "Ah, there's the bell. Please, all of you walk out."
When the meal was over all returned to the parlor, where they spent the next hour in desultory chat.;Cell division is the process by which a parent cell divides into two or more daughter cells. Cell division usually occurs as part of a larger cell cycle.
 In eukaryotes, there are two distinct types of cell division: a vegetative division, whereby each daughter cell is genetically identical to the parent cell (mitosis), and a reproductive cell division, whereby the number of chromosomes in the daughter cells is reduced by half, to produce haploid gametes (meiosis). 
Meiosis results in four haploid daughter cells by undergoing one round of DNA replication followed by two divisions: homologous chromosomes are separated in the first division, and sister chromatids are separated in the second division.
Both of these cell division cycles are used in sexually reproducing organisms at some point in their life cycle, and both are believed to be present in the last eukaryotic common ancestor. Prokaryotes also undergo a vegetative cell division known as binary fission, where their genetic material is segregated equally into two daughter cells. All cell divisions, regardless of organism, are preceded by a single round of DNA replication.;Debugging is the process of finding and resolving of defects that prevent correct operation of computer software or a system. Debugging tends to be harder when various subsystems are tightly coupled, as changes in one may cause bugs to emerge in another.
Numerous books have been written about debugging, as it involves numerous aspects, including interactive debugging, control flow, integration testing, log files, monitoring (application, system), memory dumps, profiling, Statistical Process Control, and special design tactics to improve detection while simplifying changes. The terms "bug" and "debugging" are popularly attributed to Admiral Grace Hopper in the 1940s. While she was working on a Mark II Computer at Harvard University, her associates discovered a moth stuck in a relay and thereby impeding operation, whereupon she remarked that they were "debugging" the system. However the term "bug" in the meaning of technical error dates back at least to 1878 and Thomas Edison, and "debugging" seems to have been used as a term in aeronautics before entering the world of computers.;To explain transitivity, let us look first at a totally different example that has a lot to do with transitivity but nothing to do with rationality. A combination of choices is rational if an observer can deduce someone else's preferences (that is, learn what that person likes best, medium, and least) just by observing his choices. Suppose I put your friends Adam and Ben side-by-side and I see that Adam is taller than Ben. Then I put Ben and Charlie side-by-side and I see that Ben is taller than Charlie. Can you tell me who is taller, Adam or Charlie? Adam, of course. How do we know? We simply use transitivity: if Adam is taller than Ben, and Ben is taller than Charlie, then Adam is taller than Charlie. This also means that I can rank your three friends by their height: from tallest (Adam) to shortest (Charlie).

Moyen Âge, Temps modernes, Époque contemporaine;Milieu du 19ème siècle;Moyen Âge, Temps modernes, Époque contemporaine;Deuxième quart du 19ème siècle;19ème siècle;18ème siècle;Limite entre 12ème et 13ème siècle;Limite entre 12ème et 13ème siècle;Deuxième quart du 13ème siècle

Situé en fond d’estuaire, le port de Dinan occupait dès l'époque médiévale une place importante dans le commerce international, notamment dans celui des toiles de lin et de chanvre qui étaient produites sur place et dans l'arrière pays et transportées vers l'Angleterre, les Flandres, l'Espagne puis les colonies américaines. Aux 17e et 18e siècles le port de Dinan est un point de ralliement de toute la partie sud de la Bretagne dans ses relations avec Saint-Malo, l’un des premiers ports français.
Jusqu’au milieu du 19e siècle de nouvelles activités industrielles s’y développent mais le commerce par voie d’eau peine à se maintenir concurrencé progressivement par un meilleur réseau routier avec la construction du viaduc en 1852 et l’arrivée du Chemin de fer à partir de 1879.;Le viaduc édifié entièrement en granite fait partie des grandes réalisations du milieu 19e siècle. ll facilitera les échanges entre les deux plateaux et sera à l’initiative du développement du bourg neuf de Lanvallay.;Le port est l'une des attractions de Dinan/Lanvallay. La Rance encaissée à cet endroit, traversée par un pont et un viaduc, est un lieu de toute beauté. On y ressent à la fois le poids de l'histoire et les échanges commerciaux fructueux. Ce lieu d'intenses activités a cependant beaucoup évolué depuis sa fondation monastique, à la fin du 11e siècle.;Les fours à chaux de la Ville aux Olliviers sont édifiés entre 1834 et 1836, le long du canal d'Ille-et-Rance, par Louis Leconte, armateur d'un bateau à vapeur. Il s'agit de deux fours à chaux à feu continu à courte flamme, associés à un four à plâtre qui semble avoir été construit à la même époque.;Située sur la Rance en aval de Léhon à quelques centaines de mètres de l'abbaye, l'écluse n°47 de Léhon est l'avant dernière écluse avant la mer. Le canal est ouvert à la navigation en 1832, mais la plupart des écluses ont été partiellement modifiées. En 1860 le vannage est élargi, puis vers 1894 le déversoir est réaménagé avec une passerelle métallique. La maison éclusière a été également agrandie et offre ainsi avec son petit pavillon une variante du modèle type à deux pièces en rez-de-chaussée.;L'ancien manoir de Beauvais reconstruit au 18e siècle est de nouveau réaménagé vers les années 1830 1840. Un belvédère conçu comme une petite folie surplombait anciennement la Rance. Cette demeure prestigieuse accueille aujourd'hui le prieuré sainte Anne de la Fraternité Saint Pie X.;L'abbaye de Léhon passe pour avoir été fondée dès le 9e siècle, autour de reliques de saint Magloire, évêque de Dol, dérobées à sa sépulture sur l'île anglo-normande de Serk. Après un rayonnement précoce, favorisé par l'existence d'un gué sur la voie romaine de Rennes à Corseul, les moines fuyant les Normands fondent Saint-Magloire de Paris. Ils reviennent au 11e siècle. Les premiers seigneurs de Dinan favorisent alors l’installation d'une foire et d’une petite agglomération que protège un château aménagé sur une roche dominant la Rance.;L’église abbatiale Saint-Magloire est bâtie à la fin du 12e siècle ou au début du 13e siècle. Elle présente les caractères de cette période de transition, comme le rappelle Prosper Mérimée : la porte surtout : « un arc en plein cintre retombant sur des colonnes à chapiteaux ornés de crochets, et de ces grandes feuilles dentelées encore si communes dans les premières constructions gothiques ». Elle s’inspire de modèles ligériens comme la cathédrale d'Angers par son parti d'une nef unique divisée en travées de plan carré couvertes de voûtes d'ogives bombées.;Le réfectoire de l'abbaye Saint-Magloire est le seul exemple conservé d'une telle salle en Bretagne avec celui de l'ancienne abbaye de Beauport à Paimpol. Peut-être édifié sur une construction plus ancienne comme le laisserait supposer le mur méridional, sa construction d'origine doit remonter au premier ou second quart du 13e siècle.

Key national statistics such as demographic and economic indicators (GDP, unemployment, population, etc). To satisfy this category, the following minimum criteria must be met:

  • GDP for the whole country updated at least quarterly
  • Unemployment statistics updated at least monthly
  • Population updated at least once a year
;

National government budget at a high level. This category is looking at budgets, or the planned government expenditure for the upcoming year, and not the actual expenditure. To satisfy this category, the following minimum criteria must be met:

  • Planned budget divided by government department and sub-department
  • Updated once a year.
  • The budget should include descriptions regarding the different budget sections.
;

This data category requires all national laws and statutes available to be available online, although it is not a requirement that information on legislative behaviour e.g. voting records is available. To satisfy this category, the following minimum criteria must be met:

  • Content of the law / status
  • If applicable, all relevant amendments to the law
  • Date of last amendments
  • Data should be updated at least on quarterly
;

All tenders and awards of the national/federal government aggregated by office. Monitoring tenders can help new groups to participate in tenders and increase government compliance. Data submitted in this category must be aggregated by office, updated at least monthly &, satisfy the following minimum criteria:

Tenders:

  • tenders name
  • tender description
  • tender status

Awards:

  • Award title
  • Award description
  • value of the award
  • suppliers name
;

This data category requires results by constituency / district for all major national electoral contests. To satisfy this category, the following minimum criteria must be met:

  • Result for all major electoral contests
  • Number of registered votes
  • Number of invalid votes
  • Number of spoiled ballots
  • All data should be reported at the level of the polling station
;

This data category requires a high level national map. To satisfy this category, the following minimum criteria must be met:

  • Scale of 1:250,000 (1 cm = 2.5km).
  • Markings of national roads
  • National borders
  • Marking of streams, rivers, lakes, mountains.
  • Updated at least once a year.
;

5 days forecast of temperature, precipitation and wind as well as recorded data for temperature, wind and precipitation for the past year. In order to satisfy the minimum requirements for this category, data submitted should meet the following criteria:

  • 5 days forecast of temperature updated daily
  • 5 days forecast of wind updated daily
  • 5 days forecast of precipitation updated daily
  • Historical temperature data for the past year
;

Aggregate data about the emission of air pollutants especially those potentially harmful to human health (although it is not a requirement to include information on greenhouse gas emissions). Aggregate means national-level or available for at least three major cities. In order to satisfy the minimum requirements for this category, data must be available for the following pollutants and meet the following minimum criteria:

  • Particulate matter (PM) Levels
  • Sulphur oxides (SOx)
  • Nitrogen oxides (NOx)
  • Volatile organic compounds (VOCs)
  • Carbon monoxide (CO)
  • Updated on at least once a week.
  • Measured either at a national level by regions or at leasts in 3 big cities.
;

List of registered (limited liability) companies. The submissions in this data category does not need to include detailed financial data such as balance sheet etc. To satisfy this category, the following minimum criteria must be met:

  • Name of company
  • Unique identifier of the company
  • Company address
  • Updated at least once a month
;

A database of postcodes/zipcodes and the corresponding spatial locations in terms of a latitude and a longitude (or similar coordinates in an openly published national coordinate system). If a postcode/zipcode system does not exist in the country, please submit a dataset of administrative borders. Data submitted in this category must satisfy the following minimum conditions

  • Zipcodes
  • Address
  • Coordinate (latitude longitude)
  • national level

  • updated once a year

  • Administrative boundaries

  • Boarders poligone
  • name of poligone (city, neighborhood)
  • national level
  • updated once a year
;

Data, measured at the water source, on the quality of water is essential for both the delivery of services and the prevention of diseases. In order to satisfy the minimum requirements for this category, data should be available on level of the following chemicals by water source and be updated at least weekly:

  • fecal coliform
  • arsenic
  • fluoride levels
  • nitrates
  • TDS (Total dissolved solids)
;

Cadaster showing land ownership data on a map and include all metadata on the land. Cadaster data submmitted in this category must include the following charateristics:

  • Land boarders
  • Land owners name
  • Land size
  • national level
  • updated yearly
;

Records of actual (past) national government spending at a detailed transactional level, A database of contracts awarded or similar will not considered sufficient. This data category refers to detailed ongoing data on actual expenditure. Data submitted in this category should meet the following minimum criteria:

  • Individual record of transactions.
  • Date of the transactions
  • Government office which had the transaction
  • Name of vendor
  • amount of the transaction
  • Update on a monthly basis
;

Timetables of major government operated (or commissioned) national-level public transport services (specifically bus and train). Geo location of public hospitals and health facilities with opening hours and infectious diseases rate, updated at least once a year. Data submitted in this category must include the following:

  • Location of public hospitals and clinics.
  • Data on infectious diseases rates in a country.

御前崎港を望む市道から撮影した、富士山とコンテナ船。輸出用の車両が乗船を待っている。;御前崎マリンパークから撮影した、朝焼けの富士山と風車。;田貫湖の湖面が凍結する時期の湖面を渡る風を感じる風景。;銀杏の木が黄色に色づく季節、うっすらと雪が積もった富士山。;ひな壇上の田んぼに植えられたそばの花が美しい季節のワンショット。;燃えるような新緑の季節、新茶の茶葉の息吹を感じる。富士山遠望。;日本有数の急流である富士川に設置された堰堤（頭首工）越の富士山;富士山静岡空港展望台からのショット。富士山静岡空港の名にふさわしい写真が撮れる。;富士川右岸の堤防から新幹線と富士山を入れたショット。;岩本山から梅と富士山を入れたショット。富士山には花がよく似合う。;富士山の代表的なビューポイント。富士山と駿河湾を入れた写真が撮れる。;海と富士山を入れた写真が撮れるスポット。;朝霧高原の道の駅からのショット。;休暇村富士の裏からのショット。;清水港遊覧船乗り場から帆船を入れたショット。;こどもの国からのショット。こどもの国からも富士山の素晴らしい眺望が拝める。;愛鷹山系の黒岳頂上からのショット。;越前岳登山口の展望台からのショット。意外に車で通り過ぎてしまうポイント。;水ヶ塚公園からのショット。宝永山を入れた迫力のある富士山を撮ることができる。;新幹線と富士山を入れたショット。テレビ撮影でもここからのショットが頻繁に登場する。;富士宮市の白尾山公園から桜を入れた写真。;富士宮市人穴地区から桜を入れたショット。;有料道路の料金所跡からのショット。毎年地元の人たちによって鯉のぼりが上げられている。;朝霧高原のドライブインからの鯉のぼりと富士山のショット。;日本平ホテル（現在建替中）の日本庭園からのショット。テレビドラマ「華麗なる一族」のロケが行われたことで一躍人気が出る。;日本平の展望台からのショット。眼下に清水港や三保松原等を望むことができる。富士山を眺望できる代表的なスポットの一つ;冬の雨上がりの公園の水溜りに移る逆さ富士。新雪をいただいた富士がまぶしい。;紅葉が美しい季節。山頂に近いので、富士山がデフォルメした感じ。;富士山が綺麗に見えるポイントでおなじみのところ。;農村の活気に満ちた季節感が感じられる。;空高く舞い上がる凧、まさに日本のお正月の景色。;寒桜が美しい季節、でも空は少し春霞。;薩た峠の夜明け前の静寂と車のヘッドライトの軌跡。;北駿地域の春は、菜の花から。;海岸線から遠く富士を望む。単純な構図なので、海を大きく入れて撮影。;駿河湾越の富士。手前の明神池畔の桜の時期が美しい。;朝霧高原にある富士ミルクランドからのショット。;富士山をバックに離陸準備に入るＦＤＡ（フジドリームエアライン）の５号機。他に赤、水色、ピンク、緑、紫などカラフルな機体がある。;富士山の代表的な撮影ポイントとして知られる。

In the Estonian Agricultural Registers and Information Board (ARIB), AI is used in order to detect whether the agricultural grasslands have been mowed or not using image recognition. This system, called SATIKAS, uses deep learning methods and convolutional neural network approaches to analyse the satellite data coming from the European COPERNICUS programme to automatically detect whether mowing has taken place on the Estonian grasslands.;In 2014, the Flemish Agency for Child and Family (Kind en Gezin) developed an AI system which enables more accurate predictions to detect day-care services which require further inspection. These inspections enable the agencies to keep the quality of the day-care services high and to improve the wellbeing of children.;In the municipality of Trelleborg, AI technologies are used to automate various social assistance decisions since 2016. That was the first municipality to use Robotic Process Automation (RPA) to handle various applications of social assistance.;In 2018, the Register of Enterprises of Latvia introduced a Chatbot to answer frequently asked questions regarding the process of enterprise registration. The name UNA has a symbolic meaning as it stands for Future Support of Entrepreneurs in the Latvian language. This way, UNA acts as an indicator for the future of the Latvian public administration. Chatbots are available 24/7 and thus able to make communication between citizens and the state more accessible and user friendly. UNA is available on both the website of the Register of Enterprises as well as on the Facebook page and as part of the Messenger application. UNA is able to answer frequently asked questions about the registration and liquidation of businesses, merchants, companies and organisations. If citizens already have an application in progress, they can also ask information about it.;The Swedish municipality of Upplands-Bro has started experimenting with the robot Tengai in their recruitment processes since June 2019. Tengai is one of the first interviewer robots developed with the aim to make the recruitment process less biased than traditional interview practices would do. The robot is adopted by the recruitment and staffing agency of the municipality, which has already made their recruitment processes less biased. For the last 10 years already, the agency have not used resumes in their recruitment process and growingly taken an interest in data-driven recruitment tools. Consequently, having a physical robot was regarded as the next step in preventing biases in hiring decisions. The idea behind the use of the robot was to avoid that a human person was present at the beginning of the recruitment process in order to neutralise any psycho-social prejudices.;Various municipalities in the Netherlands have been using the SyRi system to detect welfare fraud more effectively. SyRi has been developed by the Dutch government and uses various risk indicators from existing governmental systems such as taxes, health insurance, residence, education and many more, in order to detect which addresses hold a higher risk of fraud or misuse of welfare benefits.;As early as in 2012, the Polish Ministry of Labour and Social Policy (MLSP) started working on the reform of 340 labour offices (PUP - Powiatowe Urzędy Pracy), charged with analysing the trends and supporting the development of the labour market. The urgency of the reform was underlined by a general perception of PUPs being inefficient, understaffed and unfit to address the challenges posed by the modern labour market. With that reform in mind - and without significant public spending increases at hand – the MLSP has scoped possible solutions that would ensure more efficient budget allocation. In this light, resorting to an automated profiling system for unemployment came across as a modern, cost efficient and individualized method of service delivery. The process of automated profiling divides unemployed persons in three categories, taking into consideration a number of individual characteristics. Assignment to a given category determines what types of programs a beneficiary is eligible for (e.g. job placement, vocational training, apprenticeship, activation allowance). The system is based on data collected during an initial interview (e.g.. age, gender, disability and duration of unemployment), and a subsequent computer-based test that scores 24 different dimensions. Assignment to one of the three profile groups indicates the needed level of support and resource burden. Importantly, in one case categorisation translates into life-changing, binary decisions: state support or lack thereof.;The Spanish national police have adopted the VeriPol AI system in order to detect false police reports. The system was designed to be integrated into the existing Spanish National Police information system called SIDENPOL, allowing for easier use and integration into existing work practices. Its development was the result of a collaborative project between the University of Cardiff, the Charles III University of Madrid and the Spanish National Police. The database of police reports was been made available for the researchers of the universities in order to train the AI system on. For this, 1122 reports were used, including 534 true and 588 false reports.
